record_data.record_plain_text: Antelope DSR 3, LLC Electric MBR Master Interconnection Services Agreement Effective Date: February 22, 2019 Service Agreement Option Code A Attachment 1: Antelope DSR 3, LLC Service Agreement Service Agreement (Antelope DSR 3, LLC) This Service Agreement, dated as of January 24, 2019, is entered into by and between Big Sky North, LLC (the “Interconnection Provider”), and Antelope DSR 3, LLC (“User”). Reference is made to the Master Interconnection Services Agreement, dated as of August 1, 2018 (the “Master Interconnection Services Agreement”), by and among the Interconnection Provider and the other parties thereto. Capitalized terms used herein but not otherwise defined shall have the meanings assigned to such terms in the Master Interconnection Services Agreement. 1.0 Interconnection Provider shall provide 20 MW (“Reserved Capacity”) of firm transmission service to User for an initial term of 35 calendar years (the “Service Term”) following the Service Commencement Date, after the expiration of which such service shall be extended on a year-to-year basis until terminated by User upon sixty (60) days prior written notice or upon the mutual agreement of Interconnection Provider and User. 2.0 User is an Eligible Customer under the Master Interconnection Services Agreement. 3.0 User agrees to supply information the Interconnection Provider deems reasonably necessary in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice in order for it to provide the requested service. 4.0 The Interconnection Provider agrees to provide, and User agrees to take and pay for, firm transmission service over the Interconnection Facilities in accordance with the provisions of the Master Interconnection Services Agreement and this Service Agreement, with such service commencing on the date such User’s Project is Energized, which is expected to be on or about August 1, 2019 (the “Service Commencement Date”). 5.0 By execution of this Service Agreement, User hereby accedes to the Master Interconnection Services Agreement and shall hereafter have the rights and obligations of User thereunder with the same force and effect as if originally named as a User therein. The Master Interconnection Services Agreement is incorporated herein and made a part hereof. 6.0 Designated Representative of User: Randy Corey Chief Operating Officer (562) 348-1112 7.0 Summary of material terms of service. Big Sky North Substation Reserved Capacity: 20 MW Big Sky North Busbar Extension Reserved Capacity: 0 MW Total Reserved Capacity: 20 MW Does the User intend to install and/or use Managed Assets, e.g. a shared transformer? If so, please describe: No. Service Commencement Date: the date such User’s Project is Energized, expected on or about August 30, 2019 Service Term: 35 years 8.0 User (a) represents and warrants that each of the representations and warranties set forth in Section 9.1 of the Master Interconnection Services Agreement are true and correct with respect to User as of the date hereof and (b) agrees that it will perform, in accordance with the terms of the Master Interconnection Services Agreement, all the obligations that by the terms of the Master Interconnection Services Agreement are required to be performed by it as a User. [Signature page follows] IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the User and Interconnection Provider have caused this Service Agreement to be executed by their respective authorized officials effective as of the date first set forth above.
